'''Sapere aude''' is a phrase meaning "Dare to know." or "Dare to be wise". Most famously, it is found in [[Immanuel Kant]]'s essay "[[What Is Enlightenment?]]".

*'''Sapere aude''' is the school motto of the [[University of Otago]].
*'''Sapere aude''' is the school motto of the [[University of New Brunswick]].
*'''Sapere aude''' is the school motto of [[Manchester Grammar School]].
*'''Sapere aude''' is the motto of Bishop [[Hugh Oldham]], founder of [[Manchester Grammar School]].
*'''Sapere aude''' is the town motto of [[Oldham]], [[England]].

